There will be no full petrol price increase in September 2018, according to a report by BusinessTech. The report stated that the “urgent” fuel price intervention measure was announced by energy minister Jeff Radebe. Government’s intervention is a once-off, and the step was taken “because South Africans have seen sustained increases for the past five months”. The only increase that will be factored into the price for September is a retail margin increase of 4.9c per litre, to be placed on the retail price on 5 September 2018. “Despite the fact that these increases were caused mainly by international factors, the department has decided to intervene temporarily for this month,” said Radebe. Without the intervention, prices could have gone up by another 25 cents per litre, added the report. The inland petrol price for September 2018 will therefore be: